## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] {{ACCEPTANCE_CRITERION_1}}
- [ ] {{ACCEPTANCE_CRITERION_2}}
- [ ] {{ACCEPTANCE_CRITERION_3}}
- [ ] The primary user can complete the core workflow end to end through UI, auth/session, backend, data or side effects, and useful success/error feedback.
- [ ] System invariants are enforced at durable boundaries and covered by negative, retry, or recovery evidence where relevant.
- [ ] Dependency decisions include current-source evidence, verified dates, lockfile/install proof, compatibility checks, security audit output, and upgrade-path notes where relevant.
- [ ] Delivery infrastructure evidence covers CI/CD or local proof, deployability, environment/secrets, observability, health/smoke checks, rollback, and runbook notes.
- [ ] Security, observability, tests, deployment, and evidence baseline are complete or explicitly deferred with user approval.

